President Donald J. Trump has nominated Jerome H. Powell of Maryland to be the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System. Powell has been a member of the Federal Reserve's Board of Governors since May 2012 and has shown steady leadership, sound judgment, and policy expertise. He has a unique background of government service and business experience, having previously served as Under Secretary at the Department of Treasury in the administration of President George H.W. Bush. Powell has nearly three decades of business experience and holds a Bachelor of Arts in Politics from Princeton University and a Juris Doctor from Georgetown University, where he served as the editor-in-chief of the Georgetown Law Journal.